[{"id":"VH953687","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a beaker with three types of particles. There is a key in which an unshaded circle represents an A g ion with a positive 1 charge, a light shaded circle represents a C l ion with a negative 1 charge, and a dark shaded circle with 2 small unshaded circles connected represents an H 2 O molecule. There are 3 A g ions, 3 C l ions, and 14 H 2 O molecules spread throughout the beaker. At the bottom of the beaker, there is a solid composed of alternating Ag ions and Cl ions.\" height=\"245\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH953687.g02.png\" width=\"325\"></div>\n\n<p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g C l solid is in equilibrium with A g with a positive 1 charge aqueous plus C l with a negative 1 charge aqueous\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"A g C l solid is in equilibrium with A g with a positive 1 charge aqueous plus C l with a negative 1 charge aqueous\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>AgCl</mtext><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⇄</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>Ag</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">When <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g C l solid\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"A g C l solid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>AgCl</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is placed in water, it dissolves according to the chemical equation above. The particle diagram above was proposed to represent an aqueous solution in which <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g C l solid\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"A g C l solid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>AgCl</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is in equilibrium with its ions. Which of the following best explains whether or not the diagram provides a good representation of this dynamic equilibrium at the microscopic level?</p>","rubricRef":"VH953687_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is a good representation because it shows that the dipoles of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H 2 O\"><math alttext=\"H 2 O\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> molecules are oriented around the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g with a positive 1 charge\"><math alttext=\"A g with a positive 1 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Ag</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l with a negative 1 charge\"><math alttext=\"C l with a negative 1 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ions in solution.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is a good representation because it shows that the concentrations of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g with a positive 1 charge\"><math alttext=\"A g with a positive 1 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Ag</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ions and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l with a negative 1 charge\"><math alttext=\"C l with a negative 1 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ions are equal at equilibrium.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is not a good representation because it does not show that the concentration of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A g C l solid\"><math alttext=\"A g C l solid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>AgCl</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is constant at equilibrium.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is not a good representation because it does not illustrate the dynamic equilibrium in which the rates of the forward and reverse reactions are equal.</p>"],"answer":3}]